children.subject: Could you please provide more details about why she is not good? Thanks!

My friends had her when she co-taught EE20 with Babak in Spring 2015. She's obviously very talented considering she's involved in a lot of research projects and she knows the subject matter very well. However, she's apparently not a good lecturer and isn't really approachable (pretty rude actually) if you have questions or don't understand the subject matter very well.

Again I've never taken a class with her but this is a pretty much unanimous opinion all my friends had about her.
+1, zakhor was a very poor instructor imo when i took ee20. she tried teaching from slides i dont think she made, and didnt do a good job answering questions
trying to avoid Zakhor if possible. I have not heard good things about her and she's the only one teaching 123 unfortunately

Hi! I'm currently a junior in EECS trying to plan out my schedule for next semester. I've done enough CS courses, and I want to venture out into the EE field, specifically in signals and systems. Currently I'm in EE 120, CS 186, CS 168.

What are some good classes I can take if I want to go into something like robotics? (EE 126, EE 192, ...)

I've planned CS 161, EE 127, and EE 128 temporarily, but I'd like to see what other suggestions you guys have. I'm pretty clueless about what each EE course here has to offer, so any help is appreciated! Thanks!
